In a bowl, combine cookie crumbs and butter; press onto the bottom of a 9-in. springform pan coated with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 325 degrees F for 6-8 minutes. Cool on a wire rack. In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheeses until smooth; beat in sweetened condensed milk. Add eggs; beat on low speed just until combined. Beat in vanilla just until blended. In a bowl, toss 1/3 cup chocolate chips and flour; stir into batter. Pour into prepared pan. Sprinkle with remaining chocolate chips. Bake at 325 degrees F for 30-35 minutes or until almost set. Immediately run a knife around edge of pan to loosen; cool on a wire rack for 1 hour. Chill overnight. Remove sides of pan. Refrigerate leftovers.